What is HTML?
HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup Languag. It is a language made up of tags and attributes, used to create web pages and make them functional. 

A simple HTML document looks like:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Page Title</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>My First Heading</h1>
<p>My first paragraph.</p>

</body>
</html>

